Patch Set 6: Code-Review-1

(4 comments)

I'm with Dharini.

The experience has been that for any downstream operator or those who are new, openstack looks complicated. Most operators will have no context on the migrations and how the code is structured underneath. While we do have documentation or plan to add it, having it in their face puts negative impression while operating openstack.

Many people want turn key solutions. While there are ifs and buts in openstack for the same, the more comfortable an operator feels the easier it is for them to adopt and maintain openstack.

Keeping this context in mind, I think out outward facing (non-community information) like the operator release notes should be rather simple. (We can assume that developers even if not active upstream are part of community)

Patch Set 7:

Made Ian's changes.  Nikhil, the extra ws is removed when sphinx generates the target format; i always use 2 spaces after a period in RST because it's easier to see sentence breaks in monospace font that way.  I didn't change the release names to bold font because they're in plain font in the other Ocata release notes (so they'd either look weird or require us to revise all the other patches).
